A 10-year-old old boy from Ichuga village, Kieni East subcounty is hospitalised after he was set ablaze by his mother for allegedly stealing Sh100. Nyumba Kumi chairman Jackson Mbuthia says the standard three pupil  was burnt on Tuesday night last week and suffered injuries to the abdomen, ear, both hands and legs. “He is in great pain and is not attending school,” he said. The boy’s father told the Star the crime was reported at Equator patrol base on Monday. Neighbours want the mother arrested.